---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "For the keeper of the warmth",
  "description": "A page for the parent who tends the warmth around which the family forms. The Kitchen Table is a quiet meal-planning app for families. iOS beta on TestFlight.",
  "isPartOf": { "@id": "https://evoked.dev/#website" }
};
---

{/*
  Hearth Keeper archetype door - first of six per-archetype landing pages
  (Operating Plan May 2026 Task 2.2). Voice register: intimate-domestic per
  evoked-dev/CLAUDE.md "Voice Discipline Scope" addendum (Hoshi, D6.5c, 2026-05-03).

  Symbol discipline (Ishka, 2026-05-15): the archetype name "Hearth Keeper" is
  held internal-first. The page recognizes the person without first labeling
  them. The symbol surfaces lower in the page, as a name that may be offered
  back rather than imposed forward.

  Em-dashes are permitted on this surface per the addendum - they signal
  breath, hesitation, gentleness. A reviewer in founder-public discipline-mode
  should read the addendum before flagging.

  Acknowledgment-first opening per the addendum. Instability-first opening
  would feel hostile in this register.

  Voice review pending: Hoshi Sato (Voice & Tone Archetype Author, USS Enterprise).
  Build review pending: Wesley Crusher (Frontend Renderer, USS Enterprise).
  Draft author: Codex (Document Voice, USS Evoke), 2026-05-28.
*/}

<BaseLayout
  title="For the keeper of the warmth"
  description="A page for the parent who tends the warmth around which the family forms. The Kitchen Table is a quiet meal-planning app for families. iOS beta on TestFlight."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <div class="hero">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">if you've found your way here</p>
    <h1>For the keeper of the warmth</h1>
    <p class="tagline">You tend the place that holds them.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p class="lede">
      You are not the cook. You are not the manager. You are the keeper
      of the place that holds them &mdash; the warmth around which the
      family forms.
    </p>
    <p>
      That is a kind of work the world does not have good words for.
      It is mostly invisible. It rarely has a job title. And it lives
      under the hands of one person, most weeks.
    </p>
    <p>
      We see you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What's true</h2>
    <p>
      You are feeding people across more than one story.
    </p>
    <p>
      There is heritage in some of what you cook &mdash; recipes from
      a grandmother, a country, a tradition, a memory. There is what
      one child will eat and what another won't. There is what a partner
      can have and what your body needs. There are nights when someone
      is sick. There are days that are simply hard.
    </p>
    <p>
      You hold all of it. You move between it. You make decisions about
      it at five o'clock with one hand on a phone and one hand on the
      refrigerator door.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most meal-planning apps treat this as a logistics problem. We
      don't. The logistics are real, and they're not the whole thing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What we made</h2>
    <p>
      The Kitchen Table is a meal-planning app built for a family table,
      not a meal-tracking system. It holds heritage recipes as fragments,
      not as data. It lets a four-year-old be at the table. It lets a
      grandparent who only remembers <em>some kind of dumpling</em> be at
      the table.
    </p>
    <p>
      It knows when to be quiet. Grief, busy seasons, the days that are
      simply hard &mdash; the system steps back. No notifications pulling
      you toward streaks you didn't ask for. No scores. No leaderboards.
    </p>
    <p>
      No advertising. Ever. Not now, not when we're bigger.
    </p>
    <p>
      And children's profiles are unreachable to anyone outside the family.
      By architecture, not by promise.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What we won't ask you to do</h2>
    <ul class="principles">
      <li>Earn a streak.</li>
      <li>Hit a calorie target.</li>
      <li>Optimize anything.</li>
      <li>Justify a heritage recipe to a database.</li>
      <li>Perform progress when the week was hard.</li>
      <li>Pretend the work you do is smaller than it is.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The name we use, when we use one</h2>
    <p>
      Inside our team, we have a name for the work you do. We call it
      <em>keeping the hearth</em>. The hearth is the warmth around which
      the family forms. The keeper is the person who tends it.
    </p>
    <p>
      You don't have to take the name. It's a name we hold for ourselves,
      to remind us who we are building for. We are building for you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <h2>Come to the table</h2>
    <p>The Kitchen Table is in iOS beta on TestFlight. We'll write when there's something real to share.</p>
    <p class="cta-row">
      <a href="/kitchen-table/" class="btn btn-primary">See The Kitchen Table</a>
    </p>
    <form id="hearth-waitlist-form" class="waitlist-form mt-md" aria-label="Join the waitlist">
      <input type="email" id="hearth-waitlist-email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required aria-label="Email address" />
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-secondary">Join waitlist</button>
    </form>
    <p id="hearth-waitlist-status" class="waitlist-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
    <p class="form-note">No spam. No selling. Just one email when we open the door wider.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const form = document.getElementById('hearth-waitlist-form') as HTMLFormElement;
  const status = document.getElementById('hearth-waitlist-status') as HTMLParagraphElement;
  const emailInput = document.getElementById('hearth-waitlist-email') as HTMLInputElement;

  form.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const email = emailInput.value.trim();
    if (!email) return;

    status.textContent = '';
    const button = form.querySelector('button') as HTMLButtonElement;
    button.disabled = true;
    button.textContent = 'Joining...';

    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/newsletter/subscribe', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email, source: 'who/hearth-keeper' }),
      });

      if (res.ok) {
        status.textContent = 'You are in. Welcome.';
        status.className = 'waitlist-status success';
        emailInput.value = '';
      } else {
        const data = await res.json();
        status.textContent = data.error || 'Something went wrong. Try again.';
        status.className = 'waitlist-status error';
      }
    } catch {
      status.textContent = 'Something went wrong. Try again.';
      status.className = 'waitlist-status error';
    } finally {
      button.disabled = false;
      button.textContent = 'Join waitlist';
    }
  });
</script>

<style>
  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: lowercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .tagline {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .principles {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .principles li {
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .principles li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .cta-row {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .waitlist-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    max-width: 400px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .waitlist-form input[type="email"] {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
  }

  .waitlist-form input[type="email"]:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
  }

  .waitlist-form input[type="email"]::placeholder {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .waitlist-status {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    min-height: 1.2em;
  }

  .waitlist-status.success {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .waitlist-status.error {
    color: #e57373;
  }

  .form-note {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }
</style>
